The paper deals with developing an exact algorithm for solving higher-dimensional orthogonal packing problems, which involves data structures, lower bounds, and heuristics. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Among these, cs.DS is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing a tree search algorithm using a data structure for characterizing feasible packings. The other categories are also relevant as the paper deals with optimization problems, combinatorial algorithms, and geometric constraints.
